               "text": "<p class=\"desc\"><svg fill=\"none\" stroke=\"black\"> <defs> <marker id=\"arrow\" viewBox=\"0 0 10 10\" refX=\"5\" refY=\"5\" markerWidth=\"6\" markerHeight=\"6\" orient=\"auto-start-reverse\"> <path d=\"M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z\" /></marker> </defs> <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"15\" x2=\"250\" y2=\"15\" stroke=\"black\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <text x=\"270\" y=\"15\" font-size=\"1em\">A</text> <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"134\" x2=\"250\" y2=\"134\" stroke=\"black\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <text x=\"270\" y=\"134\" font-size=\"1em\">A</text> <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"114\" x2=\"250\" y2=\"114\" stroke=\"black\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <text x=\"270\" y=\"114\" font-size=\"1em\">A</text> <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"64\" x2=\"115\" y2=\"64\" stroke=\"black\" />  <line x1=\"115\" y1=\"64\" x2=\"50\" y2=\"50\" stroke=\"black\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <text x=\"35\" y=\"50\" font-size=\"1em\">B</text>  <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"36\" x2=\"155\" y2=\"36\" stroke=\"black\" /> <line x1=\"155\" y1=\"36\" x2=\"250\" y2=\"50\" stroke=\"black\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\" /> <text x=\"270\" y=\"50\" font-size=\"1em\">C</text> <circle cx=\"145\" cy=\"75\" r=\"30\"></circle> <circle cx=\"145\" cy=\"25\" r=\"7\" fill=\"#FF9999\"></circle><text x=\"143\" y=\"27\" font-size=\"1em\">-</text>  <circle cx=\"75\" cy=\"75\" r=\"7\" fill=\"#FF9999\"></circle><text x=\"73\" y=\"80\" font-size=\"1em\">-</text> <text x=\"120\" y=\"80\" font-size=\"1em\">+</text> <text x=\"140\" y=\"60\" font-size=\"1em\">+</text> <text x=\"140\" y=\"100\" font-size=\"1em\">+</text>  <text x=\"160\" y=\"80\" font-size=\"1em\">+</text> <circle cx=\"205\" cy=\"75\" r=\"7\" fill=\"#FF9999\"></circle><text x=\"202\" y=\"80\" font-size=\"1em\">-</text>  <circle cx=\"145\" cy=\"125\" r=\"7\" fill=\"#FF9999\"></circle><text x=\"143\" y=\"127\" font-size=\"1em\">-</text>  </svg></p><p class=\"desc\"><b>Graph 1</b>: Representation of Rutherford model.</p>",
               "source": [],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "Representation of Rutherford's atom, which features a large positive nucleus and small, negatively charged electrons around it.",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "#### A Different Matter\n\nBesides the particles that form atoms, during this period there was also antimatter, which, upon contact with the matter we know, annihilates (or eliminates), forming gamma radiation (<htcite0>).\n\nThe fact that matter and antimatter annihilate each other made the early universe an extremely turbulent environment. For some reason—which we are still trying to understand—an imbalance occurred as the universe cooled. As a result, we now have more matter than antimatter, although the existence of very distant regions in the universe where antimatter might still exist is not ruled out (<htcite1>).\n\n#### A Non-Visible Matter\n\nMatter and antimatter were not alone in the early universe. There is another type of matter whose composition we still do not know. However, its existence is undeniable, because measurements show that the rotation speed of a spiral galaxy is higher than expected based only on visible matter (<htcite2>).\n\n#### The First Measurements\n\nThis stage of the union of different particles—including the photon, the light particle—according to our current models, lasted about 380,000 years (<htcite3>).\n\nThis is a period for which we have no direct data to prove our theories; therefore, we conduct experiments to understand what might have happened in that time interval.\n\nFrom 380,000 years after the Big Bang, we already have observational data—light separated from matter. This first information we obtain from the primordial universe is called the Cosmic Microwave Background, and it is the topic of the next section of the *Atlas*.",
